02:21.668 --> 02:23.890
And so, isn't that how it works when you upgrade something?

02:23.910 --> 02:24.831
It's so nice.

02:24.851 --> 02:26.932
It's like, it's an improvement.

02:26.992 --> 02:29.555
If you want to know what an upgrade is in your notes, it's an improvement.

02:29.575 --> 02:31.376
It's a new version or it's an improved model.

02:31.716 --> 02:34.059
And it's just a lot of fun to upgrade things.

02:34.099 --> 02:35.780
And a lot of times around this time,

02:35.760 --> 02:38.925
of the year, what we want to do is upgrade our lives.

02:39.386 --> 02:41.028
We want to improve our relationships.

02:41.049 --> 02:42.110
We want to lose weight.

02:42.150 --> 02:43.212
We want to get in shape.

02:43.272 --> 02:49.322
We want to make a little bit more money or maybe spend less money, maybe get rid of some bad habits like drinking or smoking.

02:49.783 --> 02:53.228
It's a good time to want to upgrade your life the first of the year.

02:53.509 --> 02:57.836
The only problem is oftentimes we fail around the second week of February.

02:57.856 --> 03:01.842
80% of Americans fail in the New Year's resolutions.

03:01.890 --> 03:03.772
just six weeks into the new year.

03:04.032 --> 03:22.968
So what we said was, what if we could look into the Old Testament, into a story of perhaps the greatest upgrade ever recorded in history, and maybe draw some principles from that upgrade, apply it to our lives, and maybe this year instead of failing six weeks into the year, we can see some success with our New Year's resolutions.

03:23.008 --> 03:23.929
And so that's what we did.

03:24.289 --> 03:31.876
We looked at the story of the Israelites coming out of 400 years of slavery, moving into the Promised Land, literally a metaphor for

03:31.856 --> 03:44.293
God wants to take us out of bondage, out of slavery, and move us into a land where there's, according to the Bible, land flowing with milk and honey for the Israelites, but it's really a land of freedom.

03:44.833 --> 03:46.596
And that's what God wants to do in our life.

03:46.736 --> 03:47.837
Jesus said this one time.

03:48.098 --> 03:51.322
He said, the thief has come to steal, to kill, and to destroy.

03:51.382 --> 03:57.330
But I have come, watch this, but I have come that they may have life, and have it more than

03:57.474 --> 04:22.354
Abundantly that word means to have more than it is needed more than expected Overflowing life that's God's plan for you and me and so what we want to do is look into this story And so we started doing that last week and we saw this first principle called extreme clarity if you were here extreme clarity That's the first principle of experiencing an upgrade and the Israelites had this clarity God said hey Joshua

04:22.946 --> 04:24.368
My servant Moses is dead.

04:24.949 --> 04:30.636
Now is the time that you're going to take my people to Israelites across the Jordan River into the promised land.

04:30.656 --> 04:31.557
So that's what they had.

04:31.597 --> 04:32.578
They had that target.

04:33.059 --> 04:34.060
