05:22.793 --> 05:24.178
It's so amazing.

05:24.258 --> 05:24.899
Woo!

05:24.979 --> 05:26.360
All right, my preaching is effective.

05:26.440 --> 05:29.883
Okay, so I'm gonna assume that you all know what upgrade it is that you wanna do.

05:29.963 --> 05:33.407
Improve your marriage, improve your health and fitness, and get your finances in order.

05:33.767 --> 05:36.149
And now we're gonna look at the second principle in your notes.

05:36.169 --> 05:36.810
You're ready for this?

05:36.870 --> 05:44.537
The second principle in upgrade, we're gonna find this in the story, is that an upgrade will require you to push your, say it with me, your limits.

05:44.938 --> 05:45.638
Push your limits.

05:45.698 --> 05:48.361
We all have perceived limitations in our life.

05:49.382 --> 05:50.723
What we're capable of doing.

05:52.124 --> 05:53.906
And when we look into this story,

05:54.050 --> 06:05.806
What we're gonna find is that God, every time God wants to upgrade our lives, and we find this with the Israelites, He is going to push us past what we think we can do by ourselves.

06:05.826 --> 06:07.250
