06:58.068 --> 07:03.634
And oh, by the way, if somehow we miraculously get across the Jordan River and experience this upgrade,

07:04.002 --> 07:05.464
What are we going to fight with?

07:05.484 --> 07:06.185
We have no swords.

07:06.205 --> 07:06.906
We have no armor.

07:06.926 --> 07:07.868
We've never been in a battle.

07:07.888 --> 07:10.011
We've been wandering around in the wilderness for 40 years.

07:11.273 --> 07:14.578
None of us have ever thought or swung a sword.

07:14.678 --> 07:23.311
And the people in the land of the Promised Land, they're battle-tested, battle-ready people with living in cities that are fortified, some of them by walls.

07:24.132 --> 07:24.813
How are we going to fight?

07:24.833 --> 07:25.474
How are we going to win?

07:26.095 --> 07:27.617
Josh, I don't know.

07:27.637 --> 07:28.178
But we're going.

07:29.602 --> 07:31.345
every single upgrade.

07:31.365 --> 07:37.875
I'm telling you, when you think it's going to push you past what you think is possible in your life.

07:38.336 --> 07:44.847
Last year, I mentioned the guy named David Goggins, and I want to bring him up again because he still fascinates me.

07:44.867 --> 07:49.414
He wrote a book called You Can't Hurt Me, which is like number one seller, New York Times bestseller.

07:50.055 --> 07:54.162
And I don't recommend this book because of the colorful language in it.

07:54.306 --> 07:58.393
So that's just not something pastors can say, hey, go buy this and read it.

07:58.413 --> 08:01.719
But man, what a fascinating story this guy has.

08:01.739 --> 08:02.661
Here's a picture of David.

08:03.122 --> 08:04.665
I'll tell you a quick version of a story.

08:04.705 --> 08:18.610
He spent four years in the United States Air Force and because he had to do some things in the water, he hated the water, so he dropped out of the Air Force and started working for an extermination company and he would basically go to restaurants like, yeah, I don't

08:18.722 --> 08:23.968
I don't want to name any restaurants, but he would spray for cockroaches and vermin and things like that in these restaurants.

08:24.029 --> 08:31.778
And one night he was working and he came across what he called the motherload of cockroaches in this restaurant.

08:32.339 --> 08:35.323
And it was way more roaches that he had wanted to see in his life.

08:35.363 --> 08:38.066
And he was so down and he was so discouraged.

08:38.126 --> 08:38.607
He went home.

08:38.627 --> 08:39.648
He's like, I hate bugs.

08:39.728 --> 08:40.389
I hate roaches.

08:40.449 --> 08:41.170
I hate what I'm doing.

08:41.690 --> 08:43.913
He had gained 110 pounds.

08:43.993 --> 08:45.795
He was 190 when he was in the Air Force.

08:45.856 --> 08:47.858
Now he was up to 297.

08:48.130 --> 08:49.632
He was discouraged about his weight.

08:49.693 --> 08:50.674
He was out of shape.

08:50.774 --> 08:52.016
He was spraying for bugs.

08:53.118 --> 08:54.060
So he turns the TV on.

08:54.781 --> 08:56.143
He's like, something's got to change.

08:56.163 --> 09:00.290
And this documentary comes up on the Discovery Channel about the Navy SEALs.

09:02.754 --> 09:05.198
And he said something clicked in his mind.

09:06.120 --> 09:10.066
And he decided he was going to become a Navy SEAL.

09:10.690 --> 09:12.372
Because next day he starts calling recruiters.

09:12.392 --> 09:15.816
He said, man, I was in the Air Force for four years, and I'd like to join.

09:16.136 --> 09:17.558
And they're like, well, how tall are you?

09:17.578 --> 09:18.098
I'm 6'2".

09:18.118 --> 09:18.839
Well, how much do you weigh?

09:18.859 --> 09:19.540
297.

09:19.640 --> 09:19.820
No.

09:21.642 --> 09:23.925
You got to be 190 to be even considered.

09:25.346 --> 09:27.048
So he's like, well, how long do I have to do that?

09:27.108 --> 09:27.589
Three months.

09:28.169 --> 09:31.433
If you can lose the weight in three months, we'll consider you as a seal.

09:32.554 --> 09:34.336
So he made a decision to lose the weight.

09:35.277 --> 09:38.360
And in 85 days, I want to read to you what he did.

09:38.681 --> 09:39.762
I think it's behind you, sorry.

09:40.514 --> 09:41.375
When he reads you what he did.

09:43.117 --> 09:44.178
Nope, I don't have it.

09:44.759 --> 09:45.680
But I think I have it in my head.

09:45.720 --> 09:49.585
This is the fourth time I've given this talk.

09:49.605 --> 09:50.446
I better have it in my head.

09:51.487 --> 09:54.851
In 85 days, he committed to every single day.

09:55.131 --> 09:57.855
He rode his bike every single day for six hours.

09:59.416 --> 10:01.699
Every day, he ran a two to six mile run.

10:01.739 --> 10:04.082
He had this different loop that he would run.

10:04.386 --> 10:10.393
He would swim two miles a day, and he would do a circuit training exercise that lasted about three hours.

10:10.433 --> 10:18.423
He would do over 1,000 reps in that circuit training, all on 800 calories or less, every single day for 85 days.

10:19.825 --> 10:20.626
And he lost the weight.

10:21.387 --> 10:23.990
He lost 106 pounds in 85 days.

10:24.010 --> 10:24.931
He became an AV SEAL.

10:26.413 --> 10:30.738
He went through, he also became an Army Ranger after that, you know, small little feet there.

10:30.882 --> 10:37.634
After he left the seals in the army, he decided he was going to be an ultra marathoner, which are people that run 50-mile races, 100-mile races.

10:37.694 --> 10:40.639
He ended up running at one point over 200 miles and 39 hours.

10:41.080 --> 10:42.002
Absolutely psycho.

10:43.384 --> 10:43.985
Who does that?

10:44.526 --> 10:45.127
Who does that?

10:46.390 --> 10:55.506
Along the way, in 2013, he decided he wanted to break the pull-up record, so he did 4,000 pull-ups in 17 hours.

10:58.050 --> 11:04.797
And so he came up with this, this, when people ask him and you can go YouTube him again, the colorful language and all that stuff, you get that from the military.

11:04.817 --> 11:06.379
It's just, you gotta kind of tune that out.

11:06.439 --> 11:09.882
But when they ask him like, how did you change your life?

11:11.284 --> 11:13.706
He said, well, it's the 40% rule.

11:13.726 --> 11:14.427
I said, what's the 40% rule?

11:14.467 --> 11:22.595
He said, the 40% rule is basically when a person gets to that level in their life where they feel like they can't go anymore, they've just gone 40%.

11:22.916 --> 11:25.138
They have 60% more capacity.

11:26.210 --> 11:28.573
But at 40% things start to get uncomfortable.

11:28.814 --> 11:29.735
You start to sweat.

11:29.755 --> 11:30.856
It's like, I don't, I can't do this.

11:30.936 --> 11:35.222
It's like, I don't feel, you know, I'm in my discomfort zone.

11:35.242 --> 11:40.009
And so we tend to give up on a marriage or in our finances or with a business or with a relationship.

11:40.249 --> 11:41.791
Because it's like, I don't know if this could work.

11:41.891 --> 11:45.617
And it's at that point that you can go 60% further.

11:45.657 --> 11:47.179
And his life tells that whole story.

11:47.199 --> 11:47.840
I love what T.S.

11:47.880 --> 11:49.882
Eliot said, the famous poet.

11:50.423 --> 11:53.648
Only those who risk going too far can possibly find out how far one can go.

11:53.688 --> 11:55.410
That was Goggin's life.

11:56.866 --> 12:00.351
See, if you want to experience an upgrade, we've got to go into that 60%.

12:00.732 --> 12:05.799
We've got to push past that 40% into the discomfort zone so that we can grow.

12:05.819 --> 12:07.602
And this is exactly what there is Israelites did.

12:07.622 --> 12:08.884
They're like, I don't see any boats.

12:09.004 --> 12:09.825
I don't see a bridge.

12:09.925 --> 12:13.250
I don't know how we're going to fight the people once we get across the Jordan, but we're going.

12:13.270 --> 12:15.213
Joshua's going.

12:15.233 --> 12:16.615
And they're moving into the Promised Land.

12:16.635 --> 12:18.558
Now, when we do that, guess what happens?

12:18.578 --> 12:21.362
When we move into an area that we're uncomfortable with,

12:21.762 --> 12:26.570
Fear creeps in and doubt starts to creep in because we've never been there before.

12:26.610 --> 12:27.692
We've never done this before.

12:27.812 --> 12:28.633
It's uncomfortable.

12:28.693 --> 12:32.479
So listen to what God tells Joshua in verse six.

12:32.499 --> 12:34.463
Josh, I know this is a big deal.

12:34.563 --> 12:35.685
I know you've never done this before.

12:36.165 --> 12:38.850
So I need you to be strong and I need you to be courageous.

12:39.511 --> 12:43.477
You're going to be the one who leads these people across the Jordan to the land that I swore to their forefathers.

12:43.858 --> 12:44.519
That's verse six.

12:44.759 --> 12:45.461
Watch verse seven.

12:46.001 --> 12:47.484
Be strong and courageous.

12:47.744 --> 12:48.786
Watch verse nine.

12:49.154 --> 12:52.057
This is my command, be strong and courageous.

12:52.117 --> 12:54.780
Do not be afraid or discouraged three times.

12:55.761 --> 12:57.583
Verse six, verse seven and verse nine.

12:58.144 --> 12:58.945
What's going on here?

12:59.906 --> 13:02.088
God knows he must see the look on Joshua's face.

13:02.128 --> 13:02.969
Like I'm going to do what?

13:03.009 --> 13:03.670
