15:20.086 --> 15:26.175
And when the water below, and the water below at that point flowed onto the dead sea, into the river bed was dry.

15:26.195 --> 15:28.018
And then this happened.

15:28.418 --> 15:31.342
then all the people crossed over near the town of Jericho.

15:31.382 --> 15:39.032
Now, when we read that story, and those of you who've heard that story before, maybe in study school years ago or whatever, the focus is always on what God did.

15:39.152 --> 15:39.913
And it's awesome.

15:40.033 --> 15:47.302
God stopped this river, backed it up, dried the ground so that a million and a half people can walk across, unbelievable.

15:48.043 --> 15:48.584
But guess what?

15:48.744 --> 15:56.594
If the people didn't show up that day, if they didn't make the two mile walk, if the priest didn't put their feet in the water, why did God say, put your feet in the water?

15:57.570 --> 15:59.212
