Where do you need to push the limit?

30:31.515 --> 30:37.703
I remember a couple years ago, we launched a campus at Franklin, Franklin campus, in the old high school.

30:37.843 --> 30:38.644
Remember that Franklin?

30:38.724 --> 30:41.828
Yeah, set up tear down every single weekend.

30:42.609 --> 30:49.298
And the plan was to be in there for about a year until we found property and then build a campus and it just didn't happen.

30:50.018 --> 30:57.926
like one year turned into two years, turned into three years, and we were looking for property, we were looking at buildings, we were looking at vacant buildings, you know, open land.

30:57.986 --> 31:02.310
We just, everything, everything we looked at fell apart for like a couple of years.

31:02.931 --> 31:11.359
And then one day, I was in a restaurant with my family on Mother's Day, and this gentleman approaches me and said, hey, I heard you were looking for property in Franklin.

31:11.399 --> 31:12.941
I said, yeah, yeah, we are.

31:13.761 --> 31:18.386
And we gotta get, we gotta get Franklin out of that high school, that middle school, because it's wearing him out.

31:18.786 --> 31:22.852
He said, well, my dad has, you know, 13, 14 acres for sale.

31:22.872 --> 31:23.252
He does?

31:23.813 --> 31:24.053
Where?

31:24.253 --> 31:27.117
Oh, it's right over there by the golf course, by the interstate.

31:27.738 --> 31:29.961
I said, wow, that'd be perfect.

31:29.981 --> 31:30.923
Call me tomorrow, okay?

31:30.983 --> 31:31.483
Call him out.

31:32.605 --> 31:36.811
You know, so he starts chatting and he says, well, it's about $800,000.

31:36.871 --> 31:40.996
That's a lot of money.

31:41.016 --> 31:41.317
You agreed?

31:41.337 --> 31:41.958
That's a lot of money.

31:41.978 --> 31:43.480
$800,000.

31:43.500 --> 31:45.202
I said, okay, okay.

31:45.506 --> 31:47.709
Perfect property, Lord, you know how much this is?

31:47.789 --> 31:53.637
I felt like I was looking at Jericho, but the Jordan River was like in front of me, like $800,000.

31:53.717 --> 31:59.205
There's no bridge, there's no boats, like, how are we gonna do that?

31:59.986 --> 32:02.149
God said, talk to a few folks in the church here.

32:02.209 --> 32:03.931
So I was like, okay, I'll do that.

32:04.011 --> 32:07.876
So I called a few friends here at the church, and I told them about the property.

32:07.917 --> 32:08.978
I told them how much it was.

32:09.699 --> 32:14.866
You know, we not only raised that 800,000, but we raised even more than that to buy that property.

32:16.610 --> 32:21.156
God showed up in a big way through a few families here at this church, a few generous families.

32:21.196 --> 32:22.297
We purchased that property.

32:22.337 --> 32:23.379
We built the building.

32:23.399 --> 32:30.468
And since we built Franklin, Franklin, I know you're hearing me right now, since we built Franklin, 90 people have put their faith in Jesus Christ.

32:30.488 --> 32:30.808
Amen?

32:35.434 --> 32:36.836
We say, God, I'm counting on you.

32:36.896 --> 32:38.217
God says, well, I'm counting on you.

32:38.277 --> 32:39.399
Go talk to a few people.

32:39.619 --> 32:41.041
Go ask, go look, go hunt.

32:41.682 --> 32:42.743
And that's how it works.

32:42.763 --> 32:45.106
There's always a combined effort

32:45.378 --> 32:47.680
when we're looking for an upgrade in our lives.

32:47.720 --> 32:50.283
Look, I don't know what your upgrade is.

32:50.343 --> 32:53.466
I really don't know where to tell you or what to push on.

32:53.786 --> 32:54.847
But here's what I can tell you.

32:55.868 --> 32:58.230
You can push harder.

32:58.250 --> 32:59.231
You can push harder.

33:00.172 --> 33:01.714
God says you're the person.

33:01.754 --> 33:03.135
Let's go back to Joshua 1-6.

33:04.136 --> 33:05.858
Be strong and courageous, Josh.

33:07.579 --> 33:08.240
Because you're the one.

33:10.482 --> 33:11.023
You're the one.

33:12.944 --> 33:14.546
